SIMPLE: striped
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Striped
<hw>Striped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having stripes of
different colors; streaked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Striped bass</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Bass</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Striped maple</b></col>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a slender American tree (<spn>Acer
Pennsylvanicum</spn>) with finely striped bark. Called also
<altname>striped dogwood</altname>, and
<altname>moosewood</altname>.</cd> -- <col><b>Striped mullet</b></col>.
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See under <er>Mullet</er>, 2.</cd> --
<col><b>Striped snake</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the garter
snake.</cd> -- <col><b>Striped squirrel</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>,
<cd>the chipmunk.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strip-leaf</ent>⟦br⟧
